# ASL Recognition Project - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a real-time American Sign Language to Text & Speech converter using:
- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion
- Backend: FastAPI + Python + MediaPipe
- ML: Hand landmark detection + LSTM/Transformer models
- UI: Shadcn UI + Glassmorphism design

## Code Style

### TypeScript/React
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer `const` over `let`
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (no CSS modules)
- Use Framer Motion for animations
- Follow Shadcn UI component patterns

### Python
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Use type hints
- Use async/await for I/O operations
- Docstrings for all functions and classes

## File Organization
- Components in `src/components/`
- Pages in `src/pages/`
- Services in `src/services/`
- Backend in `backend/`
- Models in `backend/models/`

## Key Patterns

### WebSocket Communication
- Use the WebSocketService singleton
- Handle connection/disconnection gracefully
- Implement reconnection logic

### State Management
- Use React hooks (useState, useEffect, useCallback)
- Minimize prop drilling
- Use refs for mutable values

### UI Components
- All UI components should use Tailwind CSS
- Apply glassmorphism style: `bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900/40 to-slate-800/40 backdrop-blur-xl border-slate-700/50`
- Use Framer Motion for all animations
- Implement loading and error states

### Backend
- All WebSocket endpoints should validate input
- Use proper error handling
- Log important events
- Return consistent JSON responses

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `WebcamCapture.tsx`)
- Files: camelCase for services, PascalCase for components
- Functions: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- CSS classes: Tailwind utility classes

## Testing
- Test WebSocket connections
- Test camera permissions
- Test gesture recognition accuracy
- Validate model predictions

## Performance
- Optimize MediaPipe settings for performance
- Debounce rapid state updates
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Implement lazy loading where appropriate

## Accessibility
- Provide alt text for images
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Use semantic HTML
- Include ARIA labels where needed

## Documentation
- Document all public APIs
- Include examples in comments
- Update README for major changes
- Keep SETUP.md current

